body:
I have a simple assignment in a loop, like:

reg [3:0] reg_id [153:0];
reg [3:0] id_delay;
integer i;
always @(posedge clk)
     if (valid)
         for (i=0; i<=153; i=i+1)
              begin
                    reg_id[i] <= id_delay;
              end

But verilator reported errors:
Unsupported: Delayed assignment to array inside for loops.

How to solve this issue?
Why verilator can't support assignment in loop.
